Mix colors and styles to create a comfortable kitchen your family and friends love.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eModern Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/modern-kitchen-cabinets/\"\u003eModern kitchen cabinet\u003c/a\u003e doors are unembellished with sharp, straight lines. Instead of decorative details, modern cabinets generally have slab style drawers and doors without recessed or raised panels. Many of the cabinets from our Wilora Paloma frameless collections work well in modern kitchens, especially the Monte Carlo Gloss White and Marquis Dark Wood.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLook for cabinets in neutral colors such as white, grey, or dark wood. For Mid-Century modern cabinets, you want to imbue warmth and simplicity, so a natural medium-toned wood is ideal. Waterfall countertops or stainless-steel appliances complement modern cabinets well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Neutrals\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Slab style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Handles in dark metals\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nTransitional Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/transitional-kitchen-cabinets/\"\u003eTransitional kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e blend classic and modern styles into one cohesive design, but there are multiple ways to achieve this look. Combine a modern slab door with classic metal hardware. Go with a Shaker style door and modern pull hardware. Pair traditional cabinets with modern sinks and contemporary faucets. If you\u0026rsquo;re mixing elements of different styles together, you\u0026rsquo;re achieving a transitional style.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Wilora Hawthorne Eastland cabinet collection is an excellent choice for a transitional kitchen. Its raised panel, beveled door has a classic style that combines perfectly with either curved or straight modern hardware.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eColor is not associated with a transitional kitchen, so you can play with white, grey, or wood cabinets. Transitional white kitchens are bright and airy, whereas dark transitional cabinets are richly textured and dynamic.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTransitional cabinet styles are clean, uncluttered, and purposeful. While transitional is a harder kitchen design to master, the chance to create a unique style adds excitement and interest to your home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Any traditional or neutral colors in white, grey, or dark tones\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Modern or classic door frames, often with raised panels\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Curved or straight edge pulls and knobs\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Match cabinetry in style\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nFarmhouse Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFarmhouse style is all about functional comfort, spacious sinks, light colors, and functional use of space. Decorative details, such as beadboard panels and natural wood, on the island lend a Farmhouse vibe. Farmhouse blends vintage details with modern details for a clean, fresh look.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShaker style works well for \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/farmhouse-kitchen-cabinets/\"\u003efarmhouse kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e, as they\u0026rsquo;re practical. The Shaker style features a plain, rectangular frame without beveled edges, and a recessed center panel. The Wilora Hawthorne Cobbleridge White, Shaker White, or the Shaker Dove cabinet collections are ideal for adding Farmhouse flair to your new kitchen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: White, light or creamy neutrals\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Shaker or recessed\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Dark metals such as black, brushed nickel, or oil rubbed bronze\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Plain paneling on cabinets, decorative on islands\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nClassic Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe classic style focuses on traditionally timeless cabinets, d\u0026eacute;cor, and colors. Natural wood tones complemented by clean neutral colors are common with the classic style. \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/classic-kitchen-cabinets/\"\u003eClassic kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e generally have raised panel drawers and doors with decorative beveling. Add hardware finishes like brass, polished nickel, or oil-rubbed bronze for a comfortable, antique aesthetic.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDesign elements are symmetrical, without the sharp contrasts of modern styles. To do this, keep the color palette consistent. Rather than the stark contrast of black and white, opt for white and cream or grey and off-white for counters and cabinets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Creams, off whites, white, and traditional wood tones\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Decorative, raised panels\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Pulls and knobs in antique finishes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Decorative end panels, decorative crown molding\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nIndustrial Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen old warehouses were repurposed for housing and offices, the industrial style craze was born. By keeping old, raw materials, like exposed brick, pipes, and ducts, the style has a unique appeal. You can create an industrial style kitchen even if you don\u0026rsquo;t live in a loft space with brick walls and cast-iron pipes. Go for slab style door frames, large islands, and open wall shelves. A surefire option is to keep your \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/industrial-kitchen-cabinets/\"\u003eindustrial kitchen cabinet\u003c/a\u003e color palette monochrome, with light or medium wood, or grey tones. Our Wilora Hawthorne Shaker cabinet collection in Grey, is a good fit for industrial kitchen spaces.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHardware is key in an industrial style kitchen. Wrought iron, steel, or other raw, dark metals fit the style well. Lighting is another way to play up the industrial style, select fixtures with glass or iron features and exposed bulbs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Grey, wood, or monochromatic color schemes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Modern, slab, or Shaker style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Iron, steel, and knobs or pulls with black finishes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Very little molding or decoration, keep panels plain and simple\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nCottage Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe cottage style is like farmhouse but leans more towards rustic and eclectic elements. The decorative beveling on the door and drawer front panels carries a hint of elegance without ostentation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Light colors, whites, creams, or off-whites\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Beveled frames with raised panels\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Antique finishes in charming shapes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Decorative and ornate\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nWhite and Antique White Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/white-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003eWhite kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e are among the most popular colors we carry because it\u0026rsquo;s so versatile. White goes with almost every color palette or style, offering a fresh, inviting look to your kitchen. White makes small kitchens look bigger and makes the most of the light you have. Since white is a clean color, it helps your kitchen feel sparkling and orderly, even when it isn\u0026rsquo;t. But this cleanliness does come at a price, as it requires more upkeep than dark cabinets because dirt and grime is more visible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe offer a variety of shades and finishes for white cabinets \u0026ndash; glossy white, bright white, or creamy antique white. Colors: Grey, Cinder, Dove\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Raised or recessed frames, or frameless slab-style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Contrasting metals such as polished nickel, chrome, or black\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Any\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nWood Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWood has long been the premium material for kitchen cabinets, and it\u0026rsquo;s easy to see why \u0026ndash; the wood grain adds a natural and unique element to your kitchen. No two pieces of wood are the same. From muted tones to vivid multi-colored woodgrains, the comfortable texture of natural wood works well with any style kitchen, from modern to classic to farmhouse. Vevano carries primarily engineered wood, which is less expensive than real hardwood, with many of the same benefits.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMost wood cabinets are stained to highlight the unique contours of wood grain. A light stain provides a striking contrast with other elements in your kitchen while a darker stain brings out the contrast of the wood grain, providing dimension.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can paint a wood cabinet, but we don\u0026rsquo;t recommend it unless you\u0026rsquo;re refinishing your existing cabinets. Refinishing your wood cabinets with a coating of paint is an excellent way of getting a new cabinet look without the cost of replacing your cabinets, as all you need to do is sand the surface and paint the cabinets the color of your choice. However, if you\u0026rsquo;re replacing your cabinets and you don\u0026rsquo;t want a stained look, we recommend choosing cabinets made of HDF (high-density fiberboard) over wood. HDF is the better option for paint because it holds an even coat of paint more consistently than wood and doesn\u0026rsquo;t warp.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/wood-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003eWood kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e are available in a variety of door frame styles. Beveled wood doors enhance cottage kitchens, adding to a vintage feel. Plain door frames in natural wood add a modern, simple twist but also enriches the rustic feel of farmhouse kitchens.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eColors: Saddle, Chocolate, Conch Shell, Grey Wood, Oyster Shell, Dark Wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Raised or recessed frames, or frameless slab-style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Dark hardware on light cabinets, or light hardware on dark cabinets\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Any\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nDark Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhere lighter hues open a room, darker tones bring an elegance, especially when paired with contrasting light colors for countertops, flooring, appliances, and d\u0026eacute;cor. \u0026nbsp;They are easy to clean, as they hide blemishes and dirt better than white cabinets, but dark colors absorb light, making smaller kitchens feel even smaller.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/dark-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003eDark kitchen cabinets\u003c/a\u003e are available in a wide range of door frame styles, from modern frameless construction to transitional Shaker greys. Our Wilora Hawthorne Shaker Espresso collection feature a natural wood look, with deep, warm tones for classic kitchens. Colors: Cinder, Espresso, dark grey, dark wood\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Raised or recessed frames, or frameless slab-style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Contrasting colors and lighter metals like chrome or nickel\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Any\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nWhat are Kitchen Cabinets Made Of?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhether you choose to go with framed or frameless cabinets, the various components are made from different materials. At Vevano, our cabinets are durable and have plenty of character.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBox Material\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe storage area is the cabinet box. Some manufacturers use particleboard because it\u0026rsquo;s an affordable material. However, particleboard isn\u0026rsquo;t made to last and tends to sag and warp under the weight of heavy dishes and marble countertops. As such, we use plywood because it\u0026rsquo;s durable, sturdy, and lasts much longer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur framed cabinets use plywood boards with a UV-coated wood-veneered interior. Every time you open your cabinets, you show off a natural woodgrain finish, adding to the overall style.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur frameless cabinets use plywood with a white-grey linen interior infused with a durable thermofused melamine surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFramed Door Materials\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith shaker, raised, or recessed cabinets in our framed cabinet collections, the door and drawer fronts are made of five pieces \u0026ndash; a four-piece frame with a center panel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor stained cabinets, the four-piece frame is made of solid birch with a veneered MDF (medium-density fiberboard) center panel. However, our Wilora Hawthorne Wildwood Saddle cabinets are made entirely of solid birch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor painted cabinets, the frame and center panel are made of HDF (high-density fiberboard) for stability and durability. Since HDF doesn\u0026rsquo;t expand and contract like wood, it\u0026rsquo;s ideal for a framed door because the seams aren\u0026rsquo;t as likely to separate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrameless Door Material\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe frameless doors in the Wilora Paloma collection are made from engineered wood with textured melamine surfaces. The single-piece slab style doors are great for engineered wood as the wood is free to expand or contract without fear of separating seams.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nPros and Cons of Kitchen Cabinet Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSolid Birch \u0026ndash; \u003c/strong\u003ea solid board harvested from a birch tree. Commonly used for cabinets and furniture because it\u0026rsquo;s widely available and durable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eReal wood with unique grain patterns\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasy to stain\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eCan be refinished\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExpands and contracts with moisture and humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore expensive than engineered wood or fiberboard\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eSusceptible to bug infestation and rot\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eEngineered Wood with a Thermofused Melamine Surface \u0026ndash; \u003c/strong\u003ea slab made of several layers of sliced wood glued and pressed together with heat to create a board with a wood-grain textured surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore affordable than solid wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;t expand and warp to changes in humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLower quality wood material\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eCan\u0026rsquo;t be refinished\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eUses potentially harmful adhesives\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eHDF (high-density fiberboard) \u0026ndash; \u003c/strong\u003ea board made of wood fibers mixed with glues and resins and pressed together under pressure to create a dense material used for cabinet panels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTakes a consistent coat of paint very well\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExtremely hard\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStable in humid and dry environments\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;t have a wood grain\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWarps and swells when exposed to water\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLacks the lifespan of wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMDF (medium-density fiberboard) \u0026ndash; \u003c/strong\u003ea board made in similar fashion to HDF, but without as much pressure, making it lighter and less dense. Used primarily for panels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasy to paint\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLightweight\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eAffordable\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNot as durable as HDF\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWarps and swells when wet\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eShort shelf life in comparison to other materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePlywood \u0026ndash; \u003c/strong\u003ethinly sliced sheets of wood glued and pressed together while alternating woodgrain direction 90 degrees. Used for cabinet boxes, shelves, and drawer floors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;t warp or swell in high humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStable and strong enough hold heavy items\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTakes a veneer, making it easy to get a beautiful wood look without the cost\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore expensive than other engineered materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNot as strong as solid wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLow-quality plywood comes apart too easily\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParticleboard \u0026ndash;\u003c/strong\u003e a board made of sawdust, wood chips, synthetic resins and glues pressed together under heat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExtremely budget friendly\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLightweight and great for drawer boxes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eUses wood by-product and recycled materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLeast durable wood product for cabinetry\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eSags under heavy dishes, countertops, or appliances\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasily chipped or broken\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nHow to Install Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHiring a professional to install your kitchen cabinets is costly. You can expect to pay between $150 to $500 per cabinet or $150 to $350 per square foot. However, you don\u0026rsquo;t have to spend anything. While installing cabinets takes time and sweat, it isn\u0026rsquo;t overly complicated. With the right equipment, precise measurements, and a little confidence you can install your own kitchen cabinets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTake very detailed measurements of your kitchen.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFind and mark wall studs with a pencil or chalk.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMark lines to indicate where the top base cabinets will go. Typically, the top of the base cabinet is 34 \u0026frac12;\u0026rdquo; above the floor, but it can vary with desk base cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMark another line at about 53 7/8\u0026rdquo; above the floor to indicate where the bottom of the wall cabinets will be.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFinally, mark a top line to indicate the top of the cabinets at between 83 7/8\u0026rdquo; \u0026ndash; 95 7/8\u0026rdquo; (depending on the height of your wall cabinets). (Check the design plan you received from your designer for specific measurements and a more detailed install guide.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStarting with your corner wall cabinet box (without the door), use a power drill and a screw (never a nail) to secure the box to the wall by drilling through the cabinet\u0026rsquo;s back panel and into the studs. Make sure to do this at the top and bottom of the cabinet. Drill into two studs where possible. (Reference your design plan for measurements, especially for blind corner cabinets, which need a few inches of space between side walls.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWhen installing the next wall cabinet, attach the side adjacent to the mounted cabinet by clamping the sides together and screwing the two cabinet sides together.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNext, install base cabinets by starting with the corner cabinet, referring to your design packet for specific measurements.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eRepeat steps 6 and 7, secure the base cabinet to the wall studs and adjacent cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWant to install your own kitchen cabinets? Contact our design team for a custom design plan. If you\u0026rsquo;re hesitant about installing your own cabinets, we recommend hiring a professional installer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nCan I Paint Kitchen Cabinets?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYes, painting cabinets is a budget-friendly way to change the look and style of a kitchen without the cost of replacing everything. However, DIY kitchen cabinet painting is time-consuming and can get complex. The current state of your existing cabinets influences how easy your project will be.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, the surfaces of engineered wood, MDF, or HDF cabinets can\u0026rsquo;t be refinished and prepped for a new coat of paint. They require you to paint over the old color, which may not take the new paint as consistently, causing pooled areas, dripping, and inconsistent streaking.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSolid wood cabinets, however, are easy to sand and prime for a smoother painting surface. But prepping the surface is a lot of time-consuming, physical work. If the surface is painted, you need to remove the paint and sand the surface. If the surface is stained, you need to sand the surface until the stain is gone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026rsquo;re looking for an easier solution to painting your cabinets, talk to one of our designers for free about a budget solution to update your kitchen. Vevano carries a wide variety of cabinet paint colors and stain styles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nChoosing the Perfect Kitchen Cabinet Hardware and Accessories\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChanging up your kitchen accessories is a budget-friendly way to add style and function. Hardware is easy to update with changing styles and adds character to your cabinets. You can also use molding and cabinet lighting to give your cabinets a new look.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Hardware\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePulls and knobs cap off the style you\u0026rsquo;re searching for while also providing functionality to your doors and drawers. The style of a pull helps determine if a shaker cabinet is either modern, classic, or farmhouse.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKnobs are smaller than pulls, typically designed for the fingertips. They come in a variety of sizes, shapes, materials, and finishes. Glass, crystal, metal, or ceramic knobs are all options, depending on the style you\u0026rsquo;re looking for. Shapes are most often round or square but can be oval, geometric, birdcage, abstract, or more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePulls, on the other hand, are made to fit into your hand, providing greater leverage when opening and closing. This makes pulls ideal for heavy drawers and large doors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDrawer pulls are usually longer than knobs. And while the shape is different, the materials, styles, and finishes are typically the same as knobs. In fact, most pulls have knobs in the same style, allowing you to easily mix and match pulls and knobs in your kitchen without having styles clash.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Lights\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdd functionality and ambiance with under-cabinet and in-cabinet lights. Under-cabinet lighting is a strip of lights or a puck installed to the underside of wall cabinets, illuminating the wall and countertop. This helps with food preparation, cooking, and cleaning. It also brightens up the kitchen since the areas under wall cabinets are generally shadowy and dark. If you have glass-front cabinets, adding in-cabinet lights creates a sophisticated look, like museum display cases, to highlight your favorite decorative dishware. They also make finding what you want easy and fast.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Molding\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdded to the tops and bottoms of cabinets, molding adds a bit of panache and helps make your cabinets look complete and cohesive. Here are some different types of molding:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eCrown molding\u003c/em\u003e encapsulates many types of molding, but it\u0026rsquo;s a decorative piece installed to the top of the wall cabinets, either to make the cabinets look taller or create a decorative transition between the cabinets and the ceiling.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAngle Crown Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece placed between the bottom of the wall cabinet and the wall, creating a nice angled transition from the cabinet to the wall.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eLight rail molding\u003c/em\u003e goes on the outside bottom of wall cabinets, adding decorative edges while concealing under-cabinet lights.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eToe-kick molding\u003c/em\u003e covers the space between the cabinets and the floor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eScribe Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a small piece of wood used to cover inconsistencies, such as small gaps between two cabinets or where a cabinet meets a wall.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eShoe Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a rounded piece of wood used to cover inconsistencies between the toe-kick molding and the floor or the wall and the floor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eApron Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece of wood used as trim on the underside of wall cabinets or for windows near the cabinets. It\u0026rsquo;s used to conceal joints.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eBatten Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a thin strip of wood used to cover seams between panels or cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eRope Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece of wood carved to look like rope. It\u0026rsquo;s used to cover seams or add decorative details.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Panels\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKitchen cabinet panels are affixed to the exposed sides of cabinets, islands, and appliances to cover the exposed, unfinished sides of a cabinet box. Panels are available in decorative end panels, refrigerator end panels, dishwasher panels, and more. Designed to \u0026ldquo;finish\u0026rdquo; unfinished cabinets, panels are necessary to ensure a consistent look throughout your cabinets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nHow to Organize Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith so many styles, configurations, and options available, it\u0026rsquo;s easy to customize \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/cabinets-organization/\"\u003eyour cabinet organization\u003c/a\u003e to your lifestyle. Organization is key to making your cabinet storage practical.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eShelves\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile most cabinets come with shelving, there are many additional \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/cabinets-kitchen-parts-and-accessories/\"\u003ecabinet parts\u003c/a\u003e for making your life easier.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eShelf organizers for pots, pans, and their matching lids.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFloating shelves for your most used items (bowls, mugs, etc.), on eye-level shelves.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eRollout shelves as a terrific alternative to traditional shelves, making it easier to access large items.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003ePulldown shelves for accessing high items, so you don\u0026rsquo;t need a step ladder and can access items safely.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLazy Susans\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA Lazy Susan is a swiveling shelf ideal for corner cabinets where accessing the space is awkward and difficult. Perfect for containers, pots and pans, Tupperware, or snacks, a Lazy Susan provides an easier way to reach for kitchen necessities because you can turn the Lazy Susan, bringing the items to the front.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen storing containers on Lazy Susans, store lids with them or on the same shelf. These shelves are also great for storing snacks like crackers, canned food, or healthy afterschool treats.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDrawers\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDrawer organizers provide a great solution for safely storing utensils, flatware, and dishware. Large drawers are designed to accommodate stacked plates, food storage containers, mixing bowls, and more to keep your countertops free from clutter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eStore cooking utensils in drawers by type of cooking, for easy access. Drawers close to the stove are perfect for oven gloves or pot-stirring spoons. Island drawers are great for flatware, close to seating or dining areas.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpice Racks\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKeep herbs and spices arranged neatly with a spice rack. Vevano carries a variety of spice rack organizers. Choose a door-mounted spice rack for upper shelves to keep your spice shakers at eye-level. Pick a drawer organizer spice rack to easily customize any drawer and keep your spices within reach. Vevano also carries spice rack base cabinets \u0026ndash; slim 6\u0026rdquo; cabinets with rollout drawers to store spices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrash Can Pull-Outs\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMaximize your storage space with a pull-out trash can. Many pull-outs also work for recycling and compost bins, or for storing cleaning supplies. A pull-out trash can also free up floor space in your kitchen and keeps trash out of reach from pets and children.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nFAQs About Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDo you have a question about your kitchen cabinet remodel? Don\u0026rsquo;t see your question below? Contact our design team at \u003ca href=\"mailto:design@vevano.com\"\u003edesign@vevano.com\u003c/a\u003e to get your questions answered.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat color cabinets make a kitchen look bigger?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLight colors are best for making kitchens feel bigger because they reflect light, making rooms feel brighter, airy, and more spacious. White is the most reflective but colors like cream and light greys also reflect more light than darker colors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCheck out our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/white-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003ewhite kitchen cabinet collections\u003c/a\u003e for a bright kitchen, or our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/gray-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003egrey kitchen cabinet collections\u003c/a\u003e for a slightly warmer kitchen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat is the best height for kitchen cabinets?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe standard height for base cabinets is 34 \u0026frac12;\u0026rdquo; (without countertops). The bottom of your wall cabinets should be about 54\u0026rdquo; above the floor. These measurements leave enough space between your wall cabinets and your counter for appliances and cooking space. Wall cabinets themselves are typically between 30\u0026rdquo; and 42\u0026rdquo; high, depending on the design of your kitchen, the cabinet style, and height of your ceiling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhen do you need a cabinet contractor?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHire a cabinet contractor when you\u0026rsquo;re ready in start your kitchen remodel. Whether you book an installer before you order cabinets or after, have them contact us at Vevano Pro. We work with your contractor throughout the shipping, assembly, and installation process to ensure your overall satisfaction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe recommend hiring a cabinet contractor if any of the following apply to you:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYou don\u0026rsquo;t have another person to help you.\u003c/em\u003e Wall cabinets require at least two people to safely and accurately install.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYou\u0026rsquo;re unable to lift more than 20 pounds.\u003c/em\u003e Cabinets are large, so leave the heavy lifting to an expert.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYou have a time constraint.\u003c/em\u003e Installing cabinets prior to a holiday party or selling your home? Professional installers can complete the project quickly.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYour kitchen\u0026rsquo;s floorplan is complicated.\u003c/em\u003e Professionals know how to better handle an uneven floor, non-standard sizing, and electrical or plumbing issues.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDepending on the size of your kitchen, it usually takes at least 2 to 3 days for a professional to install kitchen cabinets. Give yourself plenty of time if you need your cabinets installed on a deadline.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow much does it cost to replace kitchen cabinets?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe average cost to replace your kitchen cabinets is between $2,000 and $4,000. A general rule is to plan about $100 per linear foot of kitchen. So, if you have a 10 ft wall and another 10 ft wall, that\u0026rsquo;s 20 feet for base cabinets and 20 ft for wall cabinets, or 40 linear feet and $4,000 total.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eVevano carries RTA, or ready to assemble cabinets. With these, the cost of replacing cabinets in a 10x10 kitchen is generally between $2,000 and $3,000 for a 10x10 kitchen. We\u0026rsquo;ll send you detailed instructions for you can assemble cabinets yourself or hire a professional installer to do the work for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePreassembled cabinets are a bit more expensive, as you are paying for the assembly rather than doing it yourself. They also require more storage space so prepare a section of your home or garage to house the cabinets while you wait to install them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCustom cabinets are the most expensive type of cabinetry and can set you back $7,000 to $9,000 (or more) for a 10x10 kitchen. They are best for unique layouts.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow much does it cost to install kitchen cabinets?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInstalling Your Own Cabinets\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFirst, you need tools: a hammer, ladder, miter saw, drill, stud finder, line level, clamps, and more. The average cost for tools to install kitchen cabinets is about $300 to $700. You can also save money by renting tools from your local hardware shop as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros: Save money and learn a new skill.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons: Installing your own cabinets without prior experience could result in costly mistakes, injury, or damage to your home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHiring a Cabinet Installer\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor a professional installation, plan on at least $75 per linear foot. Pricing depends on the market in your area, but for a 10x10 kitchen with 40 linear feet, installers charge about $3,000 - $5,000.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros: Trained contractors work quickly and install with more accuracy. Many installers also remove and dispose of your old kitchen cabinets for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons: Adds significant cost to your renovation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow many cabinets are in a 10x10 kitchen?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMost 10x10 kitchens usually have 10-12 cabinets: four to five base cabinets and six to seven wall cabinets. Your unique kitchen may require different quantities or types of cabinets. Some products are more common than others, such as sink base cabinets and corner cabinets for both base and wall. A bridge cabinet for over the refrigerator is also a common design element.
